### 2. Get all Flights (GET)
# Expected: 200 OK
# Response body should be a JSON array of all flights.
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/flights

### 2.1 Search Flights (GET with params)
# Expected: 200 OK
# Response body should be a JSON array containing flights from London to Paris on 2025-12-25.
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/flights/search?from=London&to=Paris&date=2025-12-25

### 3. Get Flight by ID (GET)
# Expected: 200 OK
# Response body should be the flight with ID 1.
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/flights/1

### 4. Update Flight (PUT)
# Expected: 200 OK
# Response body should be the updated flight object.
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/v1/flights/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "arrivalCity": "Manchester",
  "arrivalDate": "2025-12-20T11:15:00",
  "businessPrice": 400.00,
  "economyPrice": 140.00,
  "arrivalAirport": {
    "airportId": 3
  }
}

### 5. Verify Update (GET)
# Expected: 200 OK
# Response body should be the flight with the updated arrival city "Manchester".
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/flights/1

### 6. Test Error: Update Non-Existent Flight (PUT)
# Expected: 404 Not Found
# Error response body.
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/v1/flights/999
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "arrivalCity": "Rome",
  "arrivalAirport": {
    "airportId": 2
  }
}

